I really love this show. I've been watching it for as long as I can remember. A little while ago, I started collecting these sets. When I got the first set, it was a one-sided disc format, which I loved. Then I got the second one and later this one, and... I'm really not a fan of double-sided discs. I find them hard to handle, and they just scratch way too easily. I don't mind it too much, though, as it's the shows on the discs I really care about. However. This third set is missing one show: "The Wonderful Wizard of Ha's". I looked and it's not on it. It's supposed to come between "Moe and the Big Exit" and "Tomato Sawyer and Huckleberry Larry's Big River Rescue". Not too disappointed, though, as I still got 10 shows. I'll just have to buy the other one separately. Overall, I'm still satisfied with the product.
